The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 08 December is 9,743 (1,127.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 December, there were 513 new confirmed cases (59.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 November, there were 551 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 7% (38 fewer cases).
